<HL>
   Business Brief -- Hamilton Robinson &amp; Co.:
   New York Investment Firm
   Acquires Deutz-Allis Corp.
</HL>
<DATE>
06/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C19
</SO>
<CO>
   G.KHD WHR
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Hamilton Robinson &amp; Co., New York, said it has purchased
Deutz-Allis Corp. from Klockner-Humboldt-Deutz of Cologne,
West Germany, in a transaction valued at about $100 million.
   The transaction was financed through equity provided by
Hamilton Robinson, a private investment firm, and the sale of
Deutz-Allis's receivables to Whirlpool Financial Corp.
Deutz-Allis managers will have an equity interest in the new
company, which will be private. Hamilton Robinson didn't
break down the interests or disclose the receivables.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Deutz-Allis of Atlanta, which has annual sales of $300
million, makes combines and distributes farm implements and
tractors. Before 1985, it was part of Allis Chalmers Corp.
Klockner-Humboldt-Deutz is an industrial machinery company.
   Hamilton Robinson manages a $40 million fund for
management buy-outs and other investments.
</TEXT>
